<br>
There is NO justification whatsoever for warriors being screwed out of good 2h weapons.   The concept that knights can't dual wield as reason to give them better ratio knight only 1h weapons is reasonable.   2h weapons are a different beast entirely.   Warriors have been getting pregressively edged out of good 2h weapons since Luclin, and I rack my brain looking for justification for this, and find none.   <br>
<br>
The *only* thing I can think of is that warriors with equivalent ratio 2h weapons with better skill and triple attack would exceed in DPS a Paladin or SK.  Uhh... of COURSE, we're SUPPOSED TO! THAT is supposed to be one of our benefits of being warriors, and not having spells/utility.   Artificially blocking warriors in this manner is stupidity.   Seeing evry boss in PoP dropping a weapon that is better than warriors have access to, yet not good enough to make a Paladin switch from Goldenrod is well fuggin moronic.  Grats inventory slots, and unused weapons.<br>
