<br>
Verant is putting these dumb drops out there, like range items that have high damage and low dealy...wtf? They are one of the last classes that wanna draw aggro, but yet their weapons are designed for it. I dont know about you guys, but I beleive if a good bow comes out, a Ranger should have first priority over it. Like the Nightmare Bow, nice bow...but it procs Shadow Vortex, which used to be a big taunt for SK tanks. Why? And ofcourse being one of the better bows and the coolest design, Rangers will want it, and should get it...but why the aggro proc?<br>
<br>
I can understand them wanting to make people think and use certian weapons wisely and practice aggro control, yadda yadda, but I think theyve really gone overboard lately in giving other classes things they dont need or arent really designed for. Most warriors wouldnt give a crap about DPS if they could hold a steady taunt with out. We wouldnt crave Enraging Blow weapons, which are indeed a prosthetic, if our ability to gain taunt on our own were viable. I personally wouldnt care if every Paladin and SK in the game was walking around with 20/22 1h that proc 300pt DDs...so long as I can keep the mobs eyes on me. But until then we will have to depend on our prosthetic methods, combined with the skill of our fellow guildmates to control their own aggro. <br>
<br>
